                      edu.umaryland.igs.idea.IDEAOutputGUI
All Implemented Interfaces:
ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Serializable, Accessible, RootPaneContainer, WindowConstants
public class IDEAOutputGUI
extends JFrame

IDEAOutputGUI is the main class for the output portion of the IDEA suite, which is allow users to view results of completed analyses. It is invoked when the user selects "View Results of Previous Analysis" or "Load previous results" from the input GUI.

Method Detail

initialize

private void initialize()
The initialize method builds and displays a GUI with no data loaded. It is called when the output GUI is launched and is also called when loading results fails (to clear invalid results and/or remnants of the previously loaded results).

Parameters:

model - the model for the tree being displayed

showProgressBar

private edu.umaryland.igs.aegan.utils.SwingThreadSafeComponent<JProgressBar> showProgressBar()
The showProgressBar method creates a new progress bar in indeterminate mode, arranges it within panels, sets the top-level panel as the bottom component of the main pane and returns the newly created progress bar. This method sets the cursor to a wait cursor and disables the GUI using a glass pane. The caller is responsible for undoing both of these actions in both expected and error cases. This method should only be called from the event dispatch thread.

Returns:
a newly created progress bar in indeterminate mode, already incorporated into the GUI

load

private void load(String dirName)
The load method loads results in the specified directory. The loading is performed in a background thread so the GUI stays responsive.

Parameters:
dirName - the directory containing the .mlc files to use

treeIsVisibleAndCurrent

private boolean treeIsVisibleAndCurrent(String datasetName,
                                        String modelName)
The treeIsVisibleAndCurrent method returns true if a tree for the requested dataset and model is currently part of the display and was successfully drawn based on a tree file that is newer than the merged output (.mlc or .merged) file.

Parameters:
datasetName - the name of the requested dataset
modelName - the name of the requested model
Returns:
whether a current tree for the requested dataset and model is already drawn

displayTree

void displayTree(String datasetName,
                 String modelName)
The displayTree method parses the tree for the specified dataset and model out of the merged output file, writes the tree to a separate file, runs the Ruby program newickDraw to create a visual representation of the tree in PDF format and passes along the name of the newly-created PDF file so treeArea can display it. The data in the data table are summary results from a completed IDEA run.

Parameters:
datasetName - the name of the dataset whose tree should be displayed
modelName - the name of the model whose branch-length estimates should be used

treeArea

private JPanel treeArea(String filename)
The treeArea method returns a panel containing the IDEA logo, dataset and model selectors and a Display button above an image of the currently selected tree (if any). When the user clicks the Display button, a new tree is generated by calling the displayTree method, and then this panel is updated.

Parameters:
filename - name of the tree file to be displayed
Returns:
a panel containing the IDEA logo, dataset and model selectors, Display button and tree image (if any)

svgFilenames

private static String[] svgFilenames(String dataset,
                                     String modelNumber,
                                     File directory)
The static method svgFilenames returns a sorted array of all currently existing SVG filenames for the supplied dataset and model number in the supplied directory.

Parameters:
dataset - the dataset whose SVG files are sought
modelNumber - the model number for which SVG files are sought
directory - the directory in which SVG files are sought
Returns:
a sorted array of the names of all applicable SVG files in the directory

filledSpace

private static Dimension filledSpace(BufferedImage image)
The static method filledSpace returns the dimensions of the `interesting area' of the supplied image, which is defined as the smallest rectangular subset of the image including the upper left corner of the image such that the area of the image outside the subset is entirely white.

Parameters:
image - the image to crop
Returns:
the dimensions of the image's interesting area (a cropping of the image which includes its top left corner)

selectedSitesArea

private JPanel selectedSitesArea(String datasetIdentifier,
                                 String model)
The selectedSitesArea method returns a panel in which a display of selected sites may be shown. Two programs are executed to create the display. Because this process is time-consuming, this method should be called from a background thread, not the event dispatch thread. Although this method performs operations on Swing components, most of the operations are considered safe to perform in a background thread under the old Sun policy because they do not involve realized components (components in a hierarchy under a visible or packed window). The only exceptions are the error dialogs, which are created on the event dispatch thread.

Parameters:
datasetIdentifier - the dataset for which to display selected sites
model - the model on which to base the selected sites display
Returns:
a panel in which selected sites may be displayed
